{"lemma":"نُصْرَةُ","slug":"نُصْرَةُ","root":"ن.ص.ر","root_slug":"ن-ص-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ص-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n39909","n39910","n39917"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8F%D8%B5%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n39909","headword_ar":"نَصَرَهُ","root":"nSr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSorN","text_ar":"نَصْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSorapN","text_ar":"نُصْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) or this is a simple subst., (S, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSuwrN","text_ar":"نُصُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [but see the verse of Khidásh in what follows,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He aided"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assisted him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) namely, a person wronged, misused, or treated unjustly or injuriously, (M. A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against his enemy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he avenged him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see the verse here following, and see 8:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he supplied his want,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"somewhat thereof"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Kidásh Ibn-Zuheyr says."},{"kind":"quote","text":"faA_ino kunota ta$okuw mino xaliylK maxaAnapF\n                      \n                     \n                        ftiloka AljawaAziY EaqobuhaA wanuSuwruhaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And if thou complain of treachery from a friend. those requitals are its result and its avengers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"avengement"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: here"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSuwr","text_ar":"نُصُور"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naASirN","text_ar":"نَاصِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uhuwdN","text_ar":"شُهُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAhidN","text_ar":"شَاهِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or it may be an inf. n., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxuwlN","text_ar":"دُخُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuruwjN","text_ar":"خُرُوجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSarahu","text_ar":"تَصَرَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Eaduw~ihi","text_ar":"عَلَى عَدُوِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino Eaduw~ihi","text_ar":"مِنْ عَدُوِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSorN","text_ar":"نَصْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSorapN","text_ar":"نُصْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) or this, as remarked above, is a simple subst., (S, Msb.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(namely, God. S, A, or a man, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aided"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assisted him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strengthened him, against his enemy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he avenged him of his enemy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(See 8.)] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSarahu A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"نَصَرَهُ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God made him to be victorious, to conquer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to overcome:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the Kur, xxii. 15, where the pronoun relates to Mohammad. (TA.) In the Kur, xlvii. 8."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino tanoSuruwA A@ll~`ha yanoSurokumo","text_ar":"اـِنْ تَنْصُرُوا ا@للّٰهَ يَنْصُرْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If ye aid God's religion and his apostle, He will aid you against your enemy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"if ye aid his servants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"if ye keep his ordinances and aid his orders and comply with his commands and shun the things which He hath forbidden,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (El-Basáïr.) And the trad."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unoSuro A^axaAka ZaAlim~aA A^awo maZoluwmFA","text_ar":"اُنْصُرْ اَخَاكَ ظَالِمَّا اَوْ مَظْلُومًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is explained as meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Prevent thou thy brother from wronging when he is a wronger, and aid him against his wronger when he is wronged."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSarahu minohu","text_ar":"نَصَرَهُ مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSorN","text_ar":"نَصْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSorapN","text_ar":"نُصْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) [or the latter in this sense, as in the cases above mentioned, is a simple subst.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He served"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Preserved him from him"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSaraA@ll~`hu","text_ar":"نَصَرَا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aroDa","text_ar":"الاَرْضَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God gave rain to the earth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSara Algayovu AlA^aroDa","text_ar":"نَصَرَ الغَيْثُ الاَرْضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K,) [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSorN","text_ar":"نَصْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The rain aided the earth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"watered it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"watered it generally and copiously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and caused it to produce herbage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSara Albalada","text_ar":"نَصَرَ البَلَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it assisted the country to produce abundance of herbage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuSirati AlA^aroDo","text_ar":"نُصِرَتِ الاَرْضْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the earth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land was watered by rain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b3-  Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSarahu","text_ar":"نَصَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSorN","text_ar":"نَصْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave to him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) An Arab of the desert [in the A a beggar] accosted a people saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unoSuruwniY naSarakumu A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"اُنْصُرُونِى نَصَرَكُمُ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Give ye to me: may God give to you."},{"kind":"page_break","n":2803},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSarahu A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"نَصَرَهُ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God bestowed upon him the means of subsistence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"razaqahu","text_ar":"رَزَقَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IKtt.)"}],"source_refs":["M","A","K","S","Msb","TA","Bd","Jel"]},{"entry_id":"n39910","headword_ar":"نصّرهُ","root":"nSr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanoSiyrN","text_ar":"تَنْصِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him a Christian."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K.) It is said in a trad., [relating to the natural disposition of a child to adopt the true faith,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^abawaAhu yuhaw~idaAnihi wayunaS~iraAnihi","text_ar":"فَاَبَوَاهُ يُهَوِّدَانِهِ وَيُنَصِّرَانِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"But his two parents make him a Jew"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"make him a Christian"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n39917","headword_ar":"نُصْرَةٌ","root":"nSr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSorN","text_ar":"نَصْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in five places."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}